sentence: U.S. equities futures were more solidly in the red Wednesday after Q2 GDP was reported to have grown less than expected while fewer than predicted jobless claims were recorded for the last week.
Real gross domestic product rose 2.3% in Q2, weaker than the 2.9% expected, but within the consensus range of 1.9% to 3.5%, according to data compiled by Econoday.
Q1 GDP was revised upwards to 0.6% growth from the previously reported 0.2% contraction.
Meanwhile, jobless claims in the week to July 25 rose 267,000, less than the 272,000 expected but up from 255,000 in the previous week.
The consensus range was between 270,000 and 275,000.
In equities, Facebook ( FB ) was the most actively traded before the market opened, trading down 2.6% after reporting late Wednesday that its Q2 earnings fell on higher costs.
Consumer products giant Procter & Gamble ( PG ) was also lower 2.3% after reporting weaker-than-expected Q2 earnings.
